US$10.017 billion (2014)[1]



Net income

US$1.966 billion (2014)[1]


Total assets
US$36.131 billion (2014)[1]


Total equity
US$9.743 billion (2014)[1]



Number of employees

8,200 (2010)


Website
www.fairfax.ca


Fairfax Financial is a financial holding company based in Toronto, Ontario, which is engaged in property, casualty, and life insurance and reinsurance, investment management, and insurance claims management. The company operates primarily through several subsidiaries, including Odyssey Re, Northbridge Financial, Crum & Forster and Zenith Insurance Company.
Fairfax is led by Chairman and CEO Prem Watsa. Watsa controls nearly half of Fairfax; his value-oriented investing strategies have been compared to those of Warren Buffett.[2][3]



