Johnson & Johnson (JNJ) Shareholder Fairfax Financial Holdings LTD Can Increased Holding by $7.87 Million as Shares Rose; Agnico Eagle Mines LTD (AEM) Stock Rose While Asa Gold & Precious Metals LTD Has Cut Its Holding by $1.05 Million


					

						July 26, 2017 - By Darrin Black

Prem Watsa increased its stake in Johnson & Johnson (JNJ) by 82.56% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Fairfax Financial Holdings Ltd Can bought 68,400 shares as the company’s stock rose 6.85% with the market. The hedge fund run by Prem Watsa held 151,250 shares of the major pharmaceuticals company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $17.43 million, up from 82,850 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Fairfax Financial Holdings Ltd Can who had been investing in Johnson & Johnson for a number of months, seems to be bullish on the $349.73B market cap company. The stock declined 0.71% or $0.94 reaching $130.94 on the news. About 1.22 million shares traded. Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ) has risen 12.54% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 4.16% the S&P500.







Asa Gold & Precious Metals Ltd decreased its stake in Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd (AEM) by 5.26% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Asa Gold & Precious Metals Ltd sold 25,000 shares as the company’s stock rose 5.17% with the market. The institutional investor held 450,000 shares of the precious metals company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $18.90M, down from 475,000 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Asa Gold & Precious Metals Ltd who had been investing in Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $10.62B market cap company. The stock rose 1.89% or $0.86 reaching $46.29. About 595,498 shares traded. Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd (USA) (NYSE:AEM) has risen 7.82% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 8.88% the S&P500.
Among 16 analysts covering Agnico-Eagle Mines (NYSE:AEM), 10 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 5 Hold. Therefore 63% are positive. Agnico-Eagle Mines had 36 analyst reports since July 24, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Bank of America upgraded the stock to “Buy” rating in Wednesday, August 12 report. The firm earned “Outperform” rating on Tuesday, October 25 by Raymond James. The rating was downgraded by BMO Capital Markets to “Market Perform” on Thursday, May 12. The stock has “Hold” rating by RBC Capital Markets on Monday, June 12. As per Wednesday, March 29, the company rating was upgraded by JP Morgan. The stock of Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd (USA) (NYSE:AEM) earned “Hold” rating by Desjardins Securities on Tuesday, February 2. The rating was upgraded by BMO Capital Markets on Thursday, January 14 to “Outperform”. The rating was maintained by Barclays Capital with “Overweight” on Friday, February 12. The rating was downgraded by Raymond James to “Outperform” on Friday, October 16. As per Tuesday, August 11, the company rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets.
Asa Gold & Precious Metals Ltd, which manages about $156.72M US Long portfolio, upped its stake in Stillwater Mining Co (NYSE:SWC) by 150,000 shares to 375,000 shares, valued at $6.04M in 2016Q4, according to the filing. 
More notable recent Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd (USA) (NYSE:AEM) news were published by: Fool.ca which released: “Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd. Benefits From Rising Gold Prices” on February 03, 2017, also Fool.ca with their article: “Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd.: A Stock to Buy as Earnings Approach” published on January 20, 2017, Benzinga.com published: “Citi Looking At Gold Stocks, Says Sell Agnico Eagle Mines” on August 02, 2016. More interesting news about Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd (USA) (NYSE:AEM) were released by: Fool.ca and their article: “Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd. Was Downgraded 3 Times This Summer: Should You Sell?” published on September 07, 2016 as well as Fool.ca‘s news article titled: “Gold Stocks Rally as Agnico Eagle Mines Ltd. Reports Better Than Expected Results” with publication date: May 02, 2017.
More notable recent Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ) news were published by: Wsj.com which released: “Johnson & Johnson Raises Guidance” on July 18, 2017, also Benzinga.com with their article: “Meet Avicanna, The First Marijuana Company To Be Accepted Into Johnson …” published on July 25, 2017, Forbes.com published: “Johnson & Johnson’s Near Term Growth Likely To Remain Subdued” on July 14, 2017. More interesting news about Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ) were released by: Forbes.com and their article: “Earnings From Three Sector Giants Tomorrow: Johnson & Johnson, IBM And …” published on July 17, 2017 as well as Cnbc.com‘s news article titled: “J&J sees sales growth in near-term; raises 2017 profit forecast” with publication date: July 18, 2017.
Investors sentiment increased to 0.94 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.12, from 0.82 in 2016Q3. It is positive, as 63 investors sold JNJ shares while 834 reduced holdings. 114 funds opened positions while 731 raised stakes. 1.72 billion shares or 0.88% more from 1.71 billion shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Beech Hill Advsr reported 32,925 shares. Hugh Johnson Advsr Limited Liability Corporation owns 7,030 shares. Brown Capital Ltd Liability Corp accumulated 2,437 shares. Catawba Capital Va invested in 56,017 shares. Adage Cap Prtn Grp Limited Liability Corporation holds 3.63 million shares. Brookfield Asset Mngmt Inc holds 76,656 shares. Silvercrest Asset Mgmt Gru Lc holds 0.9% or 697,443 shares in its portfolio. Connor Clark Lunn Mngmt Limited holds 282,895 shares. Boston Common Asset Mngmt Limited Liability Corporation reported 1.64% in Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ). Reliance Tru Of Delaware owns 1.37% invested in Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ) for 78,255 shares. Iab National Bank & Trust holds 0.74% of its portfolio in Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ) for 11,359 shares. Mu holds 3.51% or 40,550 shares in its portfolio. Rench Wealth Mgmt holds 3.32% or 36,366 shares in its portfolio. Letko Brosseau And Incorporated invested in 0.84% or 793,205 shares. Cetera Advisor Limited Liability Corporation has invested 0.94% in Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ).
Since February 1, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 5 sales for $14.98 million activity. Duato Joaquin also sold $6.18 million worth of Johnson & Johnson (NYSE:JNJ) shares. 14,543 shares valued at $1.78M were sold by Kapusta Ronald A on Tuesday, February 28. 21,735 shares were sold by Ullmann Michael H, worth $2.45 million on Wednesday, February 1. $2.58 million worth of stock was sold by Stoffels Paulus on Wednesday, February 15.


