					Full Description



Fairfax Financial Holdings Limited, incorporated on November 23, 1976, is a holding company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, is engaged in property and casualty insurance, and reinsurance and investment management. The Company's segments include Insurance and Reinsurance, Runoff, Other, and Corporate and Other.The Company's subsidiaries include Northbridge Financial Corporation (Northbridge), Crum & Forster Holdings Corp (Crum & Forster), Zenith National Insurance Corp. (Zenith National), Brit Limited (Brit), Odyssey Re Holdings Corp. (OdysseyRe) and Fairfax Brasil Seguros Corporativos S.A. (Fairfax Brasil). Its other subsidiaries include Advent Capital (Holdings) Ltd. (Advent), Polskie Towarzystwo Reasekuracji Spolka Akcyjna (Polish Re) and Hamblin Watsa Investment Counsel Ltd. (Hamblin Watsa). Its Fairfax Asia includes First Capital Insurance Limited (First Capital), Falcon Insurance Company (Hong Kong) Ltd. (Falcon Insurance), The Pacific Insurance Berhad (Pacific Insurance), PT Asuransi Multi Artha Guna TBK (AMAG), Union Assurance General Limited (Union Assurance) and ICICI Lombard General Insurance Company Limited (ICICI Lombard).Insurance and ReinsuranceThe Insurance and Reinsurance segment includes Northbridge, OdysseyRe, Crum & Forster, Zenith National, Brit, Fairfax Asia, and Insurance and Reinsurance-Other. Northbridge Financial is a national commercial property and casualty insurer in Canada providing property and casualty insurance products through its Northbridge Insurance and Federated subsidiaries. OdysseyRe is a United States-based reinsurer that provides a range of property and casualty products on around the world basis, and that underwrites specialty insurance, primarily in the United States and in the United Kingdom both directly and through the Lloyd's market in London. Crum & Forster is a national commercial property and casualty insurer in the United States writing a range of commercial coverages, principally specialty coverages. Zenith National is an insurer primarily engaged in workers' compensation business in the United States. Brit is a global Lloyd's of London specialty insurer and reinsurer.Fairfax Asia includes the Company's operations that underwrite insurance and reinsurance coverages in Singapore (First Capital), Hong Kong (Falcon), Malaysia (Pacific Insurance), Indonesia (Fairfax Indonesia) and Sri Lanka (Union Assurance). Fairfax Asia also includes the Company's equity accounted interests in Mumbai-based ICICI Lombard, Vietnam-based Bank for Investment and Development of Vietnam Insurance Joint Stock Corporation (BIC Insurance) and Thailand-based Falcon Insurance PLC (Falcon Thailand).Insurance and Reinsurance-Other consists of Group Re, Advent, Polish Re, Fairfax Brasil, Colonnade Insurance S.A. (Colonnade) and Bryte Insurance Company Limited (Bryte Insurance). Group Re primarily constitutes the participation of CRC Reinsurance Limited (CRC Re) and Wentworth Insurance Company Ltd. (Wentworth) (both based in Barbados) in the reinsurance of Fairfax's subsidiaries by quota share or through participation in those subsidiaries third-party reinsurance programs on the same terms as third-party reinsurers. Group Re also writes third-party business. Advent is a specialty property reinsurance and insurance company operating through Syndicate 780 at Lloyd's. Polish Re underwrites reinsurance in Central and Eastern Europe. Fairfax Brasil writes commercial property and casualty insurance in Brazil. Colonnade is a Luxembourg insurer with branches in each of the Czech Republic, Hungary and Slovakia and also includes its insurance company, Colonnade Ukraine. Bryte Insurance is a property and casualty insurer in South Africa and Botswana.RunoffThe Runoff segment principally consists of RiverStone Insurance (UK) Limited (RiverStone (UK)), Syndicate 3500 and RiverStone Insurance Limited (RiverStone Insurance) (European runoff). It also includes TIG Insurance Company (TIG Insurance) and its subsidiary (the Unites States runoff).OtherThe Other segment consists of the Company's non-insurance operations, including Cara Operations Limited (Cara) and Original Joe's Franchise Group Inc. (Original Joe's), Keg Restaurants Ltd. (The Keg), Praktiker Hellas Commercial Societe Anonyme (Praktiker), Sporting Life Inc. (Sporting Life) and William Ashley China Corporation (William Ashley). It also includes Boat Rocker Media Inc. (Boat Rocker), Golf Town Limited (Golf Town), Pethealth Inc. (Pethealth), Thomas Cook (India) Limited (Thomas Cook India) and Fairfax India Holdings Limited (Fairfax India).Corporate and OtherThe Corporate and Other segment includes the parent entity (Fairfax Financial Holdings Limited) and its subsidiary intermediate holding companies. It also includes Hamblin Watsa, an investment management company.

